  • Enclosing class:
    GuiScreenEvent.KeyboardInputEvent

    public static class GuiScreenEvent.KeyboardInputEvent.Post
extends GuiScreenEvent.KeyboardInputEvent
    This event fires after GuiScreen.handleKeyboardInput() provided that the active screen has not been changed as a result of GuiScreen.handleKeyboardInput() and the GuiScreen.keyHandled flag has not been set. Cancel this event when you successfully use the keyboard input to prevent other handlers from using the same input.
